  "text": "The elements in MIMO systems are transmitter ( ), the receiver ( ) and the channel. The symbols and denote the number of antenna elements at transmitter and receiver sides, respectively. The system contains space-time encoder at transmission end, space-time decoder with ML detector at the reception end. Thus the MIMO channel consists of inputs and output elements, the channel matrix with outputs and inputs is represented as [( ) x ( )]. Each element of the matrix say denotes the path gain or channel transfer function between the ℎ transmit antenna and ℎ receiver antenna. Assume a quasi-static channel, that is the channel property varies randomly between two bursts but remains fixed within a transmission interval. The channel matrix with outputs and inputs can now be represented as [CITATION_1] where is the channel transfer function from ℎ transmit antenna and the ℎ receiver antenna.",
